            <title>[SOLR-3168] &quot;numberToKeep&quot; backups doesn&apos;t ever keep more than 1</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/SOLR-3168</link>
                <project id="12310230" key="SOLR">Solr</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;On &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/SOLR-2578&quot; title=&quot;ReplicationHandler Backups -- clean up old backups&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;SOLR-2578&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;SOLR-2578&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt;, Neil Hooey pointed out a silly mistake in SnapShooter.java in that I forgot to increment a counter variable in the case the user wants to keep more than 1 backup.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;I will attach a patch for this 1-line fix.  I do not intend to amend the unit test as this fix is easy to understand.  Also, the test case is already very complex and long-running.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;I will commit shortly.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
